jobs_results.title: Senior Android Developer
jobs_results.description:
Tradera is a purpose-driven company with a belief that consumption has a large impact on our planet. We‚Äôre determined to use what we control ‚Äì our business, our voice, our creativity, and our platform to do something about it.

At Tradera we‚Äôre on a mission to ‚ÄòDrive the Transition to Sustainable Shopping‚Äô, by shifting the way people consume and resell preloved goods. Our technical platform is an enabler in this shift. Together, we‚Äôre building large distributed and scalable systems handling great amounts of data. With more than five million weekly visits and 300 bids per second during peak traffic, the demands on our technical solutions are high.

To continue on our mission, we need more people to join us!

About the team
As a Senior Android Developer, you‚Äôll build our native Android app for hundreds of thousands of users in the Nordic region. You‚Äôll be critical in turning complex problems into simple, elegant solutions that elevate a world class app and user experience.

You‚Äôll play a key role in our autonomous and cross-functional app team that takes full responsibility for the app, written in Kotlin and Java. We‚Äôre a skilled group of people who like to challenge existing solutions and ways of working.

Example of responsibilities
‚Ä¢ Build a cutting edge native Android app that brings the joy of buying and selling on Sweden‚Äôs largest circular market.
‚Ä¢ Collaborate with tech, product management and UX to drive forward the next generation of our user facing app.
‚Ä¢ Ensure that our users‚Äô experience is the very best it can be.

You will work with languages and technologies such as Kotlin, Jetpack Compose
Retrofit, Realm & Room

Who are you?
We believe that you have 4+ years of experience within the area of Android Development. You value team success over personal success and care about quality, you know what it means to ship high quality code. During your career, you‚Äôve released at least one app on the Play Store or have a project in the works that you can tell us about.

Your skills
‚Ä¢ Know how to write readable, maintainable, performant object-oriented Java and Kotlin.
‚Ä¢ Deep understanding of modern Android development, e.g. Android Architectural Components, Android Jetpack, MVVM, Dagger (Hilt).
‚Ä¢ Experience with a variety of Android development tools.
‚Ä¢ The app flow contains a decent amount of Swedish, but we do welcome non-Swedish speaking applicants. We offer relocation packages if you do not currently live here.

You will have the flexibility to work from home/remotely or at our office in central Stockholm.

At Tradera we offer competitive salaries and benefits like a yearly bonus and a generous pot for competence development. But most of all, you‚Äôll get a little extra when you join us! Like a group of talented people who really love what we do and with strong belief that people deserve a smooth way to care about the planet!

Come and join us ‚Äì Don‚Äôt be square, get circular!

jobs_results.title: Android Mobile Engineer
jobs_results.description:
Now tell us if this is you

You appreciate and respect the outdoors. You might love fishing, or maybe
hiking is more your speed. Most important is that you get exicted about
working with amazing people solving challenging tasks.

Are we getting close? If so, there's a good chance you should meet us!

This is the role

We are the next generation social network focused on one of the worlds biggest
hobbies sport fishing. Only in the US there are more than 55 million people
calling themselves anglers!

We are a supercharged team of developers and we are looking forward to bring
new coders in to increase the speed of our journey. Our Android app is used by
hundreds of thousands of anglers on a daily basis. You will join as one of
three core members of our Android team. You will have large responsibilities
from day one. What you do will have actual impact on our users and Fishbrain
as a company. Your opinions and ideas will matter.

Responsibilities

Design and build advanced applications for the Android platform.

Produce high quality software using TDD, that's checked in regularly for continuous integration. Collaborate with crossfunctional teams to define, design, and ship new features.

We‚Äôre looking for a talented Android developer with a big passion for
development in general and mobile development in particular. As an Android
developer you will be a key player in the development of the platform that
Fishbrain is today.

Working with us

Our office is in city center of Stockholm, Sweden. The office has walls,
windows, multiple coffee machines, and a team of fun and amazing people
working inside it. It's also cubiclefree.

Our values

Fishing Responsibly

For us, respecting the environment is about balance. We believe in catch &
release and the sustainable harvest of fish species. Because when it comes to
the outdoors, tomorrow matters too.

Fishing Is Better with Buddies

We believe that it's more fun to brag about a catch with people who care about
fishing. These people are often called anglers. You may think that's obvious,
being an angler yourself. But on Fishbrain, your catch doesn't go headtohead
with cats doing backflips, or toddlers feeding chocolate cake to their baby
sisters.

Fishing Smarter, Not Harder

Don't get us wrong we're all for hard work, predawn wake ups to get to a
fishing spot, and getting our hands dirty. But if there's a smarter way to
fish, we're on it. It means we do the hard work of crunching catch numbers so
you don't have to.

Preferably a Bachelor's degree and/or MSc in Computer Science or equivalent
experience.

You are comfortable working with Java, Android, TDD, Git, Continuous
Integration, Open Source, RESTful APIs and dealing with UI/UX
challenges.

You feel comfortable working in Agile environments with plenty of things
going on and release cycles of two weeks.

A fast learner. Unless you're an expert in all the above, you'll need to pick up a few things along the way!

Handson. You prefer doing over talking. You can't wait to write code.
